:::summary
Economics is the social science that studies how individuals, businesses, governments, and societies allocate scarce resources to satisfy unlimited wants. It divides into **microeconomics** (the behavior of individual agents — households, firms, markets) and **macroeconomics** (the behavior of entire economies — growth, inflation, unemployment). Modern economics uses mathematical modeling, statistical analysis, and empirical research to understand and predict economic phenomena.
